  "info": {
    "title": "trunfoldlit",
    "version": "0.23.43",
    "description": "The unfoldlit command applies the unfold transform to a collection of terminal\nnodes\nfor string literal lexer rules in a grammar. An unfold operation substitutes\nthe right-hand side of a parser or lexer rule into a reference of the rule name\nthat\noccurs at the specified node. In this app, all lexer rules that have a string\nliteral\non the right-hand side of the rule are identified as the symbols to unfold in\nparser\nrules."
  },
